1
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:37,954
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

2
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:41,249
And now I need an M&A expert
who can help me

3
00:00:41,332 --> 00:00:43,209
secure management control.

4
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:55,597
REPORT ON THE STATUS
OF LARGE SHAREHOLDINGS

5
00:00:56,431 --> 00:00:57,390
Yeouido Pirates?

6
00:00:57,474 --> 00:00:59,768
I'm trying to recruit you right now,
Shin Jung-woo.

7
00:00:59,851 --> 00:01:01,770
Join Yeouido Pirates.

8
00:01:01,853 --> 00:01:04,105
First you get me kicked out of Hanmin,

9
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:05,982
and now you want me to join your side?

10
00:01:06,066 --> 00:01:07,650
Would you, if you were me?

11
00:01:08,693 --> 00:01:09,986
I would, if I were you.

12
00:01:11,946 --> 00:01:15,617
Aren't you curious how I got the money
to buy up Hanmin stocks?

13
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:18,203
How did you get it?
Did you secure a big-shot investor?

14
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:22,207
That's disappointing.
Your imagination is so limited.

15
00:01:27,962 --> 00:01:30,965
Last summer, when I was investigating
Hanmin's slush fund,

16
00:01:31,049 --> 00:01:34,552
the late President Kang Myeong-hwi,
Chairman Kang Pil-beom's son,

17
00:01:34,636 --> 00:01:36,262
had something to give me.

18
00:01:42,393 --> 00:01:43,645
Keep going, will you?

19
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:45,980
That was the end of the preview.

20
00:01:46,564 --> 00:01:48,566
Give me a straight answer
about joining me,

21
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:49,776
and I'll tell you the rest.

22
00:01:52,153 --> 00:01:54,906
You might've gotten rid of me,
but that doesn't change a thing.

23
00:01:55,573 --> 00:01:57,200
Both Chairman Kang and DK Ventures

24
00:01:57,283 --> 00:01:59,369
will do whatever it takes to survive.

25
00:02:00,829 --> 00:02:03,456
This isn't a game you can win,
so just stop now.

26
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,583
You're telling me to stand back again?

27
00:02:08,294 --> 00:02:10,588
This is why I'm trying to recruit you.

28
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:12,882
You say it won't work,
that nothing will change,

29
00:02:12,966 --> 00:02:14,592
and that I shouldn't try anything.

30
00:02:14,676 --> 00:02:18,638
I need such terrible pieces of advice
to fuel my fighting spirit.

31
00:02:35,113 --> 00:02:37,824
Hong Keum-bo,
under the Yeouido Pirates' name,

32
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:40,743
managed to buy up 9% of Hanmin's stocks.

33
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:44,706
She dared to buy
our stocks with that money?

34
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:45,665
PERSONNEL RECORD

35
00:02:45,748 --> 00:02:46,708
I mean,

36
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:49,794
she could've lived out her whole life
with that money.

37
00:02:49,878 --> 00:02:51,129
Why go through the trouble?

38
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:52,297
What's the point?

39
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:53,631
What matters is

40
00:02:54,382 --> 00:02:56,718
that the chairman's slush fund is gone.

41
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:58,761
Listen,

42
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:02,223
we can just retrieve the money
that was stolen, all right?

43
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:04,642
If we crack down hard--

44
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:05,602
No.

45
00:03:06,185 --> 00:03:07,604
Don't act rashly.

46
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:09,606
The risk is too high.

47
00:03:11,399 --> 00:03:14,235
Tail Hong Keum-bo and keep me updated
on her whereabouts and who she meets.

48
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:18,698
I need to figure out
how many insiders are involved first.

49
00:03:39,761 --> 00:03:40,845
You're back late.

50
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,723
You must be swamped at work.

51
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,391
Mr. Oh.

52
00:03:45,475 --> 00:03:48,686
Do you still meet with your former
Risk Management team?

53
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:50,605
Yeah, I guess.

54
00:03:51,272 --> 00:03:54,776
Hong Jang-mi handed in
her resignation today.

55
00:03:56,277 --> 00:03:57,862
Did she now?

56
00:03:57,946 --> 00:03:59,197
I didn't know about that.

57
00:04:00,031 --> 00:04:01,950
Did she submit it to Mr. Cha
from Research?

58
00:04:03,868 --> 00:04:05,161
Did you ever notice

59
00:04:05,745 --> 00:04:08,498
anything strange or suspicious about her
when she worked for you?

60
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:10,792
No, I didn't.

61
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:16,047
You suddenly asking me
about her is weirder, Ms. Song.

62
00:04:16,798 --> 00:04:19,592
Must I be questioned like this
in a home meant for rest…

63
00:04:21,386 --> 00:04:22,720
by someone who isn't even family?

64
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:26,891
It's tiring for us both.

65
00:04:29,143 --> 00:04:29,978
Get some rest.

66
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,367
Ms. Song asked me about you.

67
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,327
She asked if anything seemed off.

68
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:49,205
It means she's turning her suspicion
toward you too.

69
00:04:49,914 --> 00:04:50,915
Keep up the clueless act.

70
00:04:51,499 --> 00:04:52,333
Okay.

71
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:14,897
Last summer, when I was investigating
Hanmin's slush fund,

72
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:18,484
the late President Kang Myeong-hwi,
Chairman Kang Pil-beom's son,

73
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:19,944
had something to give me.

74
00:05:23,072 --> 00:05:24,365
What did he have for her?

75
00:05:25,908 --> 00:05:27,327
Is it already in her possession?

76
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:44,385
So what did President Shin say?

77
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:46,929
He got all snippy.

78
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:50,767
He may be cold,
but he isn't the type to get snippy.

79
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:53,352
Wait.

80
00:05:54,270 --> 00:05:55,104
Don't tell me…

81
00:05:56,314 --> 00:05:57,648
Were you two…

82
00:05:58,232 --> 00:05:59,901
You two are university alums.

83
00:06:00,818 --> 00:06:04,113
We graduated from the same school
and were co-workers at our first job.

84
00:06:04,197 --> 00:06:06,324
We were reunited at Hanmin
after nine years.

85
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:08,576
So were you two an item?

86
00:06:10,161 --> 00:06:11,287
It's all in the past.

87
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:16,000
No wonder you were so confident,
even with a losing case.

88
00:06:16,084 --> 00:06:18,461
You clearly had an angle to work with.

89
00:06:19,837 --> 00:06:21,422
Enough of that outdated love story.

90
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:22,882
You should quit soon too.

91
00:06:22,965 --> 00:06:26,177
It sounds like Ms. Song has caught on
and is pointing fingers now.

92
00:06:26,260 --> 00:06:27,470
Wait.

93
00:06:27,553 --> 00:06:30,807
If I resign too,
who will keep an eye on the 12th floor?

94
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:35,353
More importantly, Ms. Song's safe
is filled with all sorts of secret intel.

95
00:06:37,021 --> 00:06:38,272
Oh, right.

96
00:06:38,356 --> 00:06:41,567
Ms. Kang has left
for Switzerland by herself.

97
00:06:41,651 --> 00:06:44,695
I'm still not sure whether
that clueless girl is on our side

98
00:06:44,779 --> 00:06:47,949
or if she'll be able
to retrieve that money for us.

99
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:50,159
We'll have to wait and see.

100
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:54,163
Have you heard anything
about who the next president will be?

101
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:56,874
It sounded like Executive Director Oh
was deluding himself again.

102
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:11,180
Is Nora still in dreamland?

103
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:13,307
Nora went on a trip to Switzerland.

104
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,644
It was just a broken engagement,
not a divorce.

105
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:19,689
You could say it's a sign
of her determination to move on.

106
00:07:21,065 --> 00:07:22,859
That's a bit of a stretch.

107
00:07:24,026 --> 00:07:25,903
Staying positive and all is good,

108
00:07:25,987 --> 00:07:27,280
but in a troubled time like this,

109
00:07:27,363 --> 00:07:30,158
traveling abroad seems a bit ill-advised.

110
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:33,119
Says the wise sage.

111
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:37,748
I wanted to say this
when Nora was present,

112
00:07:37,832 --> 00:07:39,542
but now that the president's seat
is vacant,

113
00:07:40,835 --> 00:07:45,047
I believe it's time we get serious
about choosing a successor.

114
00:07:47,425 --> 00:07:51,387
I should transfer the shares
while the stock price is down,

115
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,514
so it reduces my tax burden.

116
00:07:55,224 --> 00:07:56,476
For the president's seat,

117
00:07:56,559 --> 00:07:58,352
I plan to promote internally

118
00:07:58,853 --> 00:08:00,730
rather than hire from outside.

119
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:03,149
The candidates are…

120
00:08:04,942 --> 00:08:06,152
- Albert.
- Yes, sir.

121
00:08:06,944 --> 00:08:07,778
And Nora.

122
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:09,614
Just the two of them.

123
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:11,908
Yes, sir.

124
00:08:26,797 --> 00:08:28,799
There are countless men in the world,

125
00:08:29,342 --> 00:08:32,386
but at Hanmin Investment & Securities,

126
00:08:33,971 --> 00:08:35,556
there is only one seat for the president.

127
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:37,058
It's perfect for my Nora.

128
00:08:39,852 --> 00:08:41,062
Why Switzerland, of all places?

129
00:08:41,145 --> 00:08:42,480
What?

130
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:43,439
I'm talking about Ms. Kang.

131
00:08:47,735 --> 00:08:49,028
Gosh.

132
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:50,905
After a breakup,
it's only natural for a woman

133
00:08:50,988 --> 00:08:54,534
to want to go halfway around the world,
just to be somewhere he isn't.

134
00:08:55,034 --> 00:08:56,035
You know?

135
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,790
You really know nothing
about being a woman.

136
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:02,708
Besides,

137
00:09:02,792 --> 00:09:04,669
Nora likes to eat.

138
00:09:04,752 --> 00:09:07,421
I'm sure she'll have her fill
of fondue and chocolate there.

139
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:12,718
<i>It must be a coincidence.</i>

140
00:09:13,386 --> 00:09:16,222
<i>Only the chairman and I know</i>
<i>about that Swiss account.</i>

141
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:17,932
<i>But then again,</i>

142
00:09:18,432 --> 00:09:20,935
<i>even if she did know,</i>
<i>what could that clueless girl do?</i>

143
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,280
You thought you'd be president,
didn't you?

144
00:09:32,822 --> 00:09:34,991
Son, if you become the president,

145
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:37,451
it'd be as good as me getting the job.

146
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:40,079
What if Aunt Nora becomes president?

147
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:41,539
Why would you even say that?

148
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:45,001
Never mind the ex-grandma.

149
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:46,961
What about Ms. Song?

150
00:09:50,047 --> 00:09:54,176
Song Ju-ran, that woman, is
the biggest thorn in our side right now.

151
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:58,180
She's been meeting with
Nora's mama nonstop lately,

152
00:09:58,264 --> 00:10:00,766
and she's glued to the chairman's side.

153
00:10:02,393 --> 00:10:03,853
Ms. Song is pushing for Aunt Nora.

154
00:10:11,527 --> 00:10:12,612
No matter what happens,

155
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:14,780
come hell or high water,

156
00:10:14,864 --> 00:10:17,158
you must become the new president,
understand?

157
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:18,993
That way,

158
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:21,871
you can help restore

159
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:24,081
the shares I lost, right?

160
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:31,130
We'll split the shares evenly.

161
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:32,840
Yeah.

162
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:34,508
Sure.

163
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:40,473
CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM

164
00:10:40,556 --> 00:10:43,684
You said it'd be between
Albert and Nora during breakfast,

165
00:10:44,185 --> 00:10:46,228
but do you have a preference?

166
00:10:48,314 --> 00:10:50,358
Well, it hasn't been that long

167
00:10:50,858 --> 00:10:53,653
since I've had them by my side.

168
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:57,114
Speaking of, do you have any thoughts?

169
00:10:59,408 --> 00:11:02,870
After gaining experience
in both Risk Management and Trading,

170
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:07,249
Division Manager Oh does appear
to have the makings of a capable manager.

171
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:12,046
On the other hand, Director Kang

172
00:11:13,255 --> 00:11:16,759
entered the company as a staff member
and started from the bottom.

173
00:11:17,968 --> 00:11:19,553
So I believe she would be

174
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:21,680
more closely aligned
with your management values.

175
00:11:24,058 --> 00:11:25,351
Although it was brief,

176
00:11:26,143 --> 00:11:29,355
it was a good idea
to have her work as a staff member.

177
00:11:31,941 --> 00:11:34,652
How do you plan on evaluating them?

178
00:11:36,612 --> 00:11:39,281
I'm thinking of giving them the same task.

179
00:11:40,741 --> 00:11:41,784
Let's wait and see.

180
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:55,881
All right.

181
00:11:57,425 --> 00:11:59,218
If the chairman insists,

182
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:01,846
I have no other choice.

183
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:06,016
His father selling his shares

184
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:07,977
and his ties to Hong Keum-bo…

185
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:13,607
I hold more than enough cards in my hand
to send Albert packing.

186
00:12:22,241 --> 00:12:23,242
HR Division?

187
00:12:23,951 --> 00:12:26,537
You can go ahead and process
Hong Jang-mi's resignation.

188
00:12:27,037 --> 00:12:29,290
<i>Your resignation was processed.</i>
<i>Where are you?</i>

189
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:33,169
Shin Jung-woo insisted
on confirming it for himself.

190
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:38,924
I'll call you back.

191
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:46,807
It took a lot for me to show you that,

192
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:47,892
just so you know.

193
00:12:49,685 --> 00:12:52,438
Kang Myeong-hwi, Chairman Kang's son,
was going to give you this?

194
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:54,398
Yeah.

195
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,487
What's your next target?

196
00:12:59,570 --> 00:13:01,822
The slush fund that's hidden
under Kang Nora's name

197
00:13:01,906 --> 00:13:03,032
in a Swiss account.

198
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:05,284
That's asking for trouble.

199
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:07,536
It's harder to bring assets in
than to move them out.

200
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:11,248
Foreign currency declarations,
proof of funds, and tax audits.

201
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:15,503
The tax authorities will come down on you
the moment you slip up.

202
00:13:15,586 --> 00:13:16,420
You know that.

203
00:13:16,504 --> 00:13:18,547
Kang Nora is an American citizen.

204
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:20,341
She should have no issue

205
00:13:20,424 --> 00:13:22,760
as long as it's structured as a loan
to a Korean investment firm

206
00:13:22,843 --> 00:13:26,138
with the interest rate, term,
and repayment method clearly spelled out.

207
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:27,973
- There will be an issue.
- No, there won't be.

208
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:30,476
We're talking about 100 billion won.
How could there not be an issue?

209
00:13:32,436 --> 00:13:34,688
He meant 100 won, as in two 50-won coins.

210
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:39,151
No need to broadcast it.

211
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:41,070
This is precisely why I asked to see you.

212
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:43,155
How are you so sure
that Kang Nora will take your side?

213
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:46,575
Kang Nora is in Switzerland right now.

214
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:48,869
Switzerland, understand?

215
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:30,619
Stop playing so hard to get.

216
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:35,666
Then again, this is exactly why
I want to recruit you.

217
00:14:36,625 --> 00:14:38,460
I need you to butt in and hit the brakes

218
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:40,504
when I can't see the light has turned red.

219
00:15:05,112 --> 00:15:06,322
You all know who this is.

220
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:08,240
He's our new member, Shin Jung-woo.

221
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:10,743
I'm Shin Jung-woo.

222
00:15:12,036 --> 00:15:14,496
Sir, I once went
to submit a report to you.

223
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:16,081
I'm currently working in the IT--

224
00:15:16,165 --> 00:15:17,833
Of course I remember you,

225
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:18,792
Mr. Lee Yong-gi.

226
00:15:19,376 --> 00:15:21,462
This house suddenly feels so cramped.

227
00:15:21,545 --> 00:15:22,796
I wonder why.

228
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:25,049
Can we trust him?

229
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:28,344
You too, Ms. Go?

230
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:30,596
You see, we're operating

231
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:32,640
purely on trust right now,
without any contracts.

232
00:15:32,723 --> 00:15:33,557
I see.

233
00:15:33,641 --> 00:15:35,476
I also agreed to join without a contract.

234
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:37,019
Why?

235
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:38,562
To get revenge on my grandpa?

236
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:41,315
To prevent costly mistakes.

237
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:45,194
I can cover Keum-bo's legal blind spots
and emotional judgment.

238
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:48,656
I guess you could call me
her rational partner.

239
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:49,865
Oh my, a "partner"?

240
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:52,910
A partner?

241
00:15:57,081 --> 00:16:01,460
To start, the funds Chairman Kang
laundered and moved offshore

242
00:16:01,543 --> 00:16:03,212
will be difficult to bring back.

243
00:16:03,754 --> 00:16:05,756
So for all of you,

244
00:16:05,839 --> 00:16:11,261
the only lawful, practical way
to quickly participate

245
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:14,098
in the management of Hanmin…

246
00:16:15,349 --> 00:16:16,517
- "All of you"?
- "All of you"?

247
00:16:17,726 --> 00:16:18,769
Right.

248
00:16:18,852 --> 00:16:20,062
Let me rephrase that.

249
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:21,939
All of you and I…

250
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:25,943
I mean, <i>we </i>will…

251
00:16:26,026 --> 00:16:28,487
We'll be cleaning out
all the domestic slush funds.

252
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:31,115
We start with borrowed-name accounts
that Seoul branch managers

253
00:16:31,198 --> 00:16:32,908
opened under their families.

254
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:37,454
I remember thinking
how strange it was back then.

255
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:40,416
- Your performance has been stellar lately.
- Thanks.

256
00:16:40,499 --> 00:16:42,418
I'm so envious of you.
Tell us your secret.

257
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:45,546
Hello, everyone.

258
00:16:48,090 --> 00:16:50,050
- It's nice to see you all again.
- Hello.

259
00:16:50,634 --> 00:16:52,636
- Have you been well?
- Yes, ma'am. Thank you.

260
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:54,805
- We've met before, right?
- Yes, it's been a while.

261
00:16:55,389 --> 00:16:57,349
- Nice to see you.
- You're still as beautiful as ever.

262
00:16:57,433 --> 00:17:00,102
- It's nice to see you again.
- Yes, nice to see you.

263
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:02,938
We need to allocate some funds…

264
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:04,982
The branch managers were under her thumb

265
00:17:05,065 --> 00:17:07,401
when she wasn't even in charge of sales.

266
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:09,862
I assumed it was because
she was in the chairman's inner circle.

267
00:17:10,446 --> 00:17:12,156
Even when the New Korea Fund
was being sold,

268
00:17:12,239 --> 00:17:14,575
Chairman Kang had Ms. Song
oversee the branches.

269
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:16,243
I found that odd as well.

270
00:17:17,244 --> 00:17:19,538
The ledger only has
the names of the branch managers

271
00:17:19,621 --> 00:17:20,873
and their balances,

272
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:23,000
so we suspect that Song Ju-ran

273
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:25,502
has the bankbooks
and seals in her possession.

274
00:17:27,755 --> 00:17:29,131
Ms. Song's safe.

275
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:31,592
That's the gold mine.

276
00:17:32,926 --> 00:17:33,802
Her safe?

277
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:40,059
YEOUIDO PIRATES

278
00:17:40,142 --> 00:17:41,602
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

279
00:17:41,685 --> 00:17:43,896
EPISODE 14: THE ERA OF GREAT PIRATES

280
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:31,360
Ms. Go.

281
00:18:38,742 --> 00:18:40,577
I have perfect pitch.

282
00:18:53,757 --> 00:18:54,675
Damn.

283
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:10,274
We need a key?

284
00:19:19,616 --> 00:19:20,742
It's open.

285
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:22,119
It's open!

286
00:19:24,621 --> 00:19:25,455
SEALS

287
00:19:39,303 --> 00:19:40,137
BRANCH MANAGER

288
00:19:41,346 --> 00:19:42,181
SAENARA BANK

289
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:45,684
VIP.

290
00:19:54,610 --> 00:19:55,652
SAENARA BANK

291
00:20:04,244 --> 00:20:05,412
What's taking him so long?

292
00:20:08,665 --> 00:20:09,583
Let's see.

293
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:13,837
Seals, branch managers,

294
00:20:14,755 --> 00:20:15,589
and VIPs.

295
00:20:15,672 --> 00:20:16,590
They're identical.

296
00:20:22,846 --> 00:20:23,680
There we go.

297
00:20:30,938 --> 00:20:32,064
Wait.

298
00:20:42,199 --> 00:20:43,992
We have the seals and the bankbooks.

299
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:47,120
She even wrote down
the usernames and passwords.

300
00:20:47,621 --> 00:20:49,998
We just need to withdraw it all
through online banking.

301
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:52,834
You wrapped it up properly, right?

302
00:20:52,918 --> 00:20:54,086
Of course.

303
00:20:54,169 --> 00:20:55,796
I'm a seasoned pro.

304
00:21:43,677 --> 00:21:44,678
Good.

305
00:21:44,761 --> 00:21:47,848
Now it's time to work your magic,
Mr. Lee and Mr. Shin.

306
00:21:48,807 --> 00:21:51,018
Should we start buying
as soon as the money's ready?

307
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:55,147
No, we need to make the rounds
of all the Seoul branches.

308
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:57,441
- That's how rumors will start.
- Okay.

309
00:21:58,025 --> 00:21:59,276
Why so friendly?

310
00:21:59,359 --> 00:22:00,360
Oh, right.

311
00:22:00,444 --> 00:22:01,820
We're university alums.

312
00:22:03,405 --> 00:22:04,656
It sounds like you were very close.

313
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:06,783
Was it a sibling dynamic?

314
00:22:08,285 --> 00:22:10,370
Boys, focus on what I'm saying.

315
00:22:11,496 --> 00:22:12,539
"Boys."

316
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:17,210
Now, we're going to split up the branches.

317
00:22:19,963 --> 00:22:22,507
SLUSH FUNDS IN BRANCHES ACROSS SEOUL

318
00:22:22,591 --> 00:22:23,800
MASEOK BANK, JOGEOK BANK

319
00:22:23,884 --> 00:22:27,179
NARA BANK, NONGJU BANK,
CHUNGSEO BANK, SAENARA BANK, FARMERS' BANK

320
00:22:27,262 --> 00:22:28,096
ALL EMPTIED OUT

321
00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:30,307
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

322
00:24:07,821 --> 00:24:09,239
How's Go Bok-hee doing?

323
00:24:09,322 --> 00:24:11,825
She seems anxious
ever since President Shin resigned.

324
00:24:11,908 --> 00:24:14,786
She even combs through
the newspaper job listings during work.

325
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:16,788
Is that so?

326
00:24:36,516 --> 00:24:37,601
I did it.

327
00:24:44,274 --> 00:24:46,359
Yeouido Pirates' main page is back online.

328
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:48,361
Now that the server is overseas,

329
00:24:48,445 --> 00:24:51,239
it can't be forcibly shut down
like last time.

330
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:53,200
Not a chance.

331
00:24:59,289 --> 00:25:03,335
YEOUIDO PIRATES
MAIN MENU, COMMUNITY, ETC.

332
00:25:07,505 --> 00:25:08,340
It's true.

333
00:25:09,633 --> 00:25:11,426
Yeouido Pirates is back.

334
00:25:12,385 --> 00:25:13,803
Do I have to register again?

335
00:25:14,721 --> 00:25:15,889
Well…

336
00:25:15,972 --> 00:25:19,559
I heard the head of IT was able to log in
with his old username and password.

337
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:22,646
That old-school man found out before me?

338
00:25:26,274 --> 00:25:28,526
Ever since Mr. So and Mr. Bang left,

339
00:25:29,319 --> 00:25:30,362
I feel so left out.

340
00:25:31,613 --> 00:25:34,824
I'm too much out of the loop
when it comes to stuff like this.

341
00:25:34,908 --> 00:25:37,535
You should've been
looking out for me, Mr. Lee.

342
00:25:37,619 --> 00:25:39,412
That's why I'm here, sir.

343
00:25:42,415 --> 00:25:44,918
I heard people
in the IT Division talking earlier.

344
00:25:45,001 --> 00:25:48,129
They say rumors about someone
aggressively buying up large amounts

345
00:25:48,213 --> 00:25:50,298
of Hanmin stocks
are spreading like wildfire.

346
00:25:52,550 --> 00:25:54,010
Since the IMF crisis started,

347
00:25:54,094 --> 00:25:57,889
our stocks have plunged over 60%.

348
00:25:57,973 --> 00:25:59,683
Who would buy financial stocks

349
00:26:00,183 --> 00:26:01,226
when they're in free fall?

350
00:26:02,602 --> 00:26:04,229
- Them.
- What?

351
00:26:04,813 --> 00:26:07,232
YEOUIDO PIRATES

352
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:12,487
Unbelievable.

353
00:26:13,613 --> 00:26:15,448
HELD BY: YEOUIDO PIRATES
CEO: HONG KEUM-BO

354
00:26:27,627 --> 00:26:29,879
This Yeouido Pirates business.

355
00:26:29,963 --> 00:26:33,883
Shin Jung-woo shut this down last time,
didn't he?

356
00:26:34,634 --> 00:26:35,510
Yes, sir.

357
00:26:35,593 --> 00:26:38,179
We shut down
the PC communication community,

358
00:26:38,763 --> 00:26:41,808
but it appears they have established
an independent website.

359
00:26:43,101 --> 00:26:44,352
These bastards

360
00:26:45,145 --> 00:26:47,480
even set up an investment trust company,

361
00:26:47,564 --> 00:26:50,275
and now they're buying up
our company stocks?

362
00:26:51,192 --> 00:26:53,403
And who is this Hong Keum-bo

363
00:26:53,486 --> 00:26:55,071
listed as their CEO?

364
00:26:55,864 --> 00:26:57,907
I believe they're the leader
of Yeouido Pirates.

365
00:26:58,491 --> 00:26:59,326
Its captain.

366
00:26:59,951 --> 00:27:00,785
"Captain"?

367
00:27:00,869 --> 00:27:05,290
Yes, their nickname is
"The Captain" in the community.

368
00:27:05,373 --> 00:27:06,416
What a clown, right?

369
00:27:06,499 --> 00:27:10,003
Their name only surfaced
after the company was registered.

370
00:27:11,671 --> 00:27:13,006
Good grief.

371
00:27:22,766 --> 00:27:23,933
Listen carefully.

372
00:27:25,185 --> 00:27:26,061
Between Albert

373
00:27:26,644 --> 00:27:27,479
and Nora,

374
00:27:28,104 --> 00:27:29,189
I will appoint

375
00:27:29,856 --> 00:27:32,942
whoever catches the Captain first

376
00:27:33,026 --> 00:27:35,153
as the president.

377
00:27:45,038 --> 00:27:46,539
How dare they…

378
00:27:53,630 --> 00:27:54,881
Yahoo!

379
00:27:54,964 --> 00:27:57,384
Son, if we just catch Yeouido Pirates,

380
00:27:57,467 --> 00:27:59,010
the president's seat will be yours.

381
00:27:59,969 --> 00:28:00,845
President Oh.

382
00:28:02,555 --> 00:28:03,473
Dad.

383
00:28:03,556 --> 00:28:05,350
We're nowhere close to finding them.

384
00:28:06,059 --> 00:28:07,102
It's just a matter of time.

385
00:28:07,852 --> 00:28:11,147
I'll utilize all my connections
and intel networks

386
00:28:11,231 --> 00:28:13,900
to make you the president, okay?

387
00:28:16,403 --> 00:28:17,237
Okay.

388
00:28:18,822 --> 00:28:21,324
Remember, Captain Hook
was defeated by Peter Pan.

389
00:28:24,494 --> 00:28:26,329
Shin Jung-woo.

390
00:28:26,913 --> 00:28:28,581
DK Ventures.

391
00:28:30,291 --> 00:28:33,169
And now Yeouido Pirates.

392
00:28:34,045 --> 00:28:37,507
Is Hanmin surrounded by hostile forces,

393
00:28:38,174 --> 00:28:39,634
just waiting to strike?

394
00:28:41,970 --> 00:28:43,263
I'm telling you,

395
00:28:43,346 --> 00:28:46,224
they're trying to take what's not theirs
without even lifting a finger.

396
00:28:48,268 --> 00:28:50,061
You're still going strong.

397
00:28:50,562 --> 00:28:53,106
This could all blow over
without much trouble, like last time.

398
00:28:53,982 --> 00:28:55,108
But you know,

399
00:28:55,984 --> 00:28:58,236
that name, Hong Keum-bo…

400
00:28:59,654 --> 00:29:02,991
I've heard that name somewhere before.

401
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:07,162
I'll look into it.

402
00:29:08,121 --> 00:29:08,955
All right.

403
00:29:17,964 --> 00:29:19,048
Here.

404
00:29:23,219 --> 00:29:25,722
You look awfully glum
for the sole survivor.

405
00:29:25,805 --> 00:29:27,766
Do you have the world on your shoulders?

406
00:29:27,849 --> 00:29:28,683
They're so droopy.

407
00:29:29,350 --> 00:29:30,185
Understaffed.

408
00:29:30,268 --> 00:29:31,352
Overworked.

409
00:29:31,436 --> 00:29:32,729
Stressed.

410
00:29:33,438 --> 00:29:35,607
All the employees
are working themselves to the bone,

411
00:29:35,690 --> 00:29:36,691
but the higher-ups

412
00:29:36,775 --> 00:29:39,277
are throwing everything they have
into the succession battle.

413
00:29:39,861 --> 00:29:42,781
Well, the chairman despises taxes.

414
00:29:43,573 --> 00:29:46,075
The mere mention of them,
and he'd call the country a thief.

415
00:29:46,701 --> 00:29:48,036
I'm sure he's trying
to transfer the shares

416
00:29:48,119 --> 00:29:51,289
when the stock price has dropped
to save on inheritance tax.

417
00:29:52,332 --> 00:29:55,376
At this rate, Albert might really
become the president.

418
00:29:56,586 --> 00:29:58,963
Speaking of which,
maybe I should've invited Big Al too?

419
00:29:59,047 --> 00:30:00,673
Oh, and Hong Jang-mi.

420
00:30:00,757 --> 00:30:02,717
I heard Ms. Hong
was transferred to Research.

421
00:30:02,801 --> 00:30:04,010
How is she doing?

422
00:30:04,093 --> 00:30:06,930
Ms. Hong held out
during the second restructuring,

423
00:30:07,931 --> 00:30:09,057
but she ended up quitting.

424
00:30:11,518 --> 00:30:14,729
She really went out of her way
to make life difficult for herself.

425
00:30:18,441 --> 00:30:19,275
Hello?

426
00:30:20,276 --> 00:30:21,528
Yes, Executive Director Oh!

427
00:30:23,988 --> 00:30:24,823
Yes.

428
00:30:26,741 --> 00:30:28,368
How have you been doing, Bang?

429
00:30:29,536 --> 00:30:31,955
Are you looking for a new job?

430
00:30:33,581 --> 00:30:35,208
I've submitted my résumé everywhere,

431
00:30:36,125 --> 00:30:37,043
but it hasn't been easy.

432
00:30:39,838 --> 00:30:41,589
Times are tough.

433
00:30:42,966 --> 00:30:45,134
I mean, all my kids are all grown up,

434
00:30:46,219 --> 00:30:48,137
so I can live off of my savings.

435
00:30:48,638 --> 00:30:51,266
But you're still
in your prime years right now.

436
00:30:53,643 --> 00:30:57,063
I could check if any smaller
financial institutions are hiring for you.

437
00:30:57,146 --> 00:31:01,276
No, I don't want to be
handling money anymore.

438
00:31:06,447 --> 00:31:08,825
See that? It's like I'm always on call.

439
00:31:09,909 --> 00:31:11,286
Come on,

440
00:31:11,369 --> 00:31:14,622
how the hell am I supposed to find
the Captain of Yeouido Pirates?

441
00:31:15,248 --> 00:31:16,457
If I had such talents,

442
00:31:16,541 --> 00:31:18,543
I would've left Yeouido years ago!

443
00:31:21,004 --> 00:31:23,548
- Have a drink.
- No, I have to work early tomorrow.

444
00:31:25,133 --> 00:31:26,509
I told you.

445
00:31:26,593 --> 00:31:28,344
You should've fired Ms. Hong back then.

446
00:31:28,428 --> 00:31:31,347
Why in the world
did you sacrifice yourself, Bang?

447
00:31:33,975 --> 00:31:35,810
Look at you, laughing it off again.

448
00:31:38,396 --> 00:31:39,314
Damn it.

449
00:31:42,233 --> 00:31:45,361
Get your <i>gimbap</i> here.

450
00:31:46,613 --> 00:31:49,407
They're 1,000 won each.

451
00:31:49,490 --> 00:31:50,533
BLOWOUT SALE

452
00:31:57,999 --> 00:32:00,418
<i>Ms. Hong held out</i>
<i>during the second restructuring,</i>

453
00:32:00,501 --> 00:32:01,878
but she ended up quitting.

454
00:32:03,171 --> 00:32:05,590
She really went out of her way
to make life difficult for herself.

455
00:32:10,219 --> 00:32:11,095
I'll take a <i>gimbap</i>.

456
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:13,556
Excuse me.

457
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:16,768
- Sir!
- Yes?

458
00:32:16,851 --> 00:32:17,936
One <i>gimbap</i>, please.

459
00:32:18,019 --> 00:32:19,771
Sure. That'll be 1,000 won.

460
00:32:20,355 --> 00:32:22,398
All right. Thank you.

461
00:32:37,372 --> 00:32:38,289
<i>Gimbap </i>for sale.

462
00:32:40,541 --> 00:32:41,417
Thank you.

463
00:32:41,501 --> 00:32:42,585
- Thank you.
- Goodbye.

464
00:32:44,379 --> 00:32:47,006
It's late. Go home with Bom.

465
00:32:49,717 --> 00:32:50,718
I'll close up with you.

466
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:52,428
You're back at work tomorrow.

467
00:32:52,512 --> 00:32:54,931
It's a long commute to Seoul,
so you need your sleep.

468
00:32:55,014 --> 00:32:56,099
I don't think I can sleep.

469
00:32:58,226 --> 00:32:59,185
You know,

470
00:32:59,268 --> 00:33:02,146
it's really nice having you around
and helping us out.

471
00:33:02,230 --> 00:33:05,191
If work gets too tough,
you can always open a sister chicken shop.

472
00:33:05,274 --> 00:33:08,194
I'll give you a great deal
on the secret recipe.

473
00:33:08,277 --> 00:33:09,821
You've got some nerve.

474
00:33:12,991 --> 00:33:14,951
I saw a nice storefront for rent recently.

475
00:33:16,119 --> 00:33:17,036
It's close by.

476
00:33:17,954 --> 00:33:20,164
I'm being serious. Think about it, okay?

477
00:33:23,710 --> 00:33:26,045
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES
MAGANG BRANCH

478
00:33:31,300 --> 00:33:33,177
Let's have another productive day today.

479
00:33:33,261 --> 00:33:35,304
- Yes, sir.
- Let's get ready to open.

480
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:42,854
She's really something else.

481
00:33:42,937 --> 00:33:44,230
I wouldn't come back if I were her.

482
00:33:44,313 --> 00:33:46,149
No branch manager
would be happy to see her.

483
00:33:46,232 --> 00:33:47,567
She was a total nuisance.

484
00:33:48,151 --> 00:33:49,861
Did you hear about the settlement she got?

485
00:33:49,944 --> 00:33:51,154
- Really?
- Yeah.

486
00:33:52,071 --> 00:33:53,156
Who told you that?

487
00:33:54,032 --> 00:33:56,909
I didn't get a single cent.

488
00:34:10,590 --> 00:34:12,633
Why can't you do it?

489
00:34:12,717 --> 00:34:15,678
You said you could before,
so you should do it now.

490
00:34:15,762 --> 00:34:17,972
Are you kidding me right now, huh?

491
00:34:18,056 --> 00:34:19,140
Do you think I'm a joke?

492
00:34:19,223 --> 00:34:20,349
<i>I'm really sorry, ma'am.</i>

493
00:34:20,433 --> 00:34:21,893
<i>I got all the documents</i>
<i>you told me to get!</i>

494
00:34:21,976 --> 00:34:24,187
I will sue you!

495
00:34:26,647 --> 00:34:29,525
Get me the branch manager right now.

496
00:34:30,526 --> 00:34:33,696
You said I could get the loan before,
so give me the loan now.

497
00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:35,990
This young lady says I can't!

498
00:34:36,074 --> 00:34:38,409
Hurry up and check. Now!

499
00:34:39,702 --> 00:34:41,287
Where are you going?

500
00:34:41,871 --> 00:34:42,955
Ma'am.

501
00:34:43,581 --> 00:34:44,665
Let me show you to my office.

502
00:34:45,249 --> 00:34:48,586
No, I'd like Ms. Kim Mi-sook
to handle my account.

503
00:34:50,755 --> 00:34:52,298
Can you deposit this as available funds?

504
00:35:03,101 --> 00:35:04,018
Did you see

505
00:35:04,644 --> 00:35:07,855
how the branch manager's face lit up
with each stack I pulled out?

506
00:35:08,898 --> 00:35:10,858
All I did was
deposit the money you brought,

507
00:35:10,942 --> 00:35:12,944
but I feel like
I already earned my keep today.

508
00:35:13,027 --> 00:35:16,239
The branch manager actually smiled
when he sent me off for lunch.

509
00:35:18,157 --> 00:35:21,536
It's just money that won't sit for long
before it's used to buy stocks.

510
00:35:24,038 --> 00:35:26,207
Are your coworkers giving you a hard time?

511
00:35:29,335 --> 00:35:32,296
Everyone was happy to see me
and welcomed me back.

512
00:35:34,048 --> 00:35:35,883
I'm ready to start working hard again.

513
00:35:38,636 --> 00:35:40,221
You don't have to try too hard.

514
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:44,308
I learned that if you try too hard,

515
00:35:44,392 --> 00:35:46,102
you end up feeling wronged at some point.

516
00:35:49,897 --> 00:35:54,318
But you're also working hard on something.

517
00:35:55,611 --> 00:35:57,196
I hope it works out for you.

518
00:35:59,240 --> 00:36:01,200
I hope that for me too.

519
00:36:04,370 --> 00:36:05,288
Eat up.

520
00:36:32,899 --> 00:36:33,858
Hello?

521
00:36:35,443 --> 00:36:36,611
Okay, we'll be right down.

522
00:36:42,241 --> 00:36:44,827
Big Al and Ms. Go
are waiting for us at the restaurant.

523
00:36:44,911 --> 00:36:46,412
- Takeout for me, please.
- Takeout for me, please.

524
00:36:48,539 --> 00:36:50,499
Okay, I'll pick up two servings.

525
00:36:55,171 --> 00:36:56,172
Why is it just you?

526
00:36:56,923 --> 00:36:59,383
Captain Hong and President Shin
asked for takeout.

527
00:37:04,722 --> 00:37:05,556
They're so similar.

528
00:37:06,140 --> 00:37:08,726
Their work styles, focus,
and even their approach to life.

529
00:37:09,310 --> 00:37:10,728
They used to be a couple, after all.

530
00:37:16,567 --> 00:37:17,735
- A couple?
- What?

531
00:37:17,818 --> 00:37:18,653
For how long?

532
00:37:18,736 --> 00:37:21,614
I'm not sure how long it lasted,
but they broke up nine years ago.

533
00:37:22,198 --> 00:37:23,032
Nine years…

534
00:37:24,158 --> 00:37:26,369
Then there's nothing to worry about.

535
00:37:26,869 --> 00:37:28,120
I still have a chance.

536
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,414
Who are you trying to beat?

537
00:37:31,082 --> 00:37:33,292
The dumbfounded Mr. Lee Yong-gi here?

538
00:37:33,376 --> 00:37:34,919
That's why they were so friendly.

539
00:37:35,002 --> 00:37:36,504
I see now.

540
00:37:36,587 --> 00:37:38,756
Their work styles, focus…

541
00:37:39,340 --> 00:37:41,926
That's why they were so similar. I see…

542
00:37:43,469 --> 00:37:46,055
Let's forget this side quest
and focus on the main one.

543
00:37:46,639 --> 00:37:48,474
Especially you, future President Al.

544
00:37:59,652 --> 00:38:01,821
<i>Tell your father at his office tomorrow</i>

545
00:38:01,904 --> 00:38:03,990
that you found
the Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

546
00:38:18,838 --> 00:38:21,090
Come on now, Mr. Nam.

547
00:38:21,173 --> 00:38:23,759
The Financial Supervisory Service
must have

548
00:38:23,843 --> 00:38:26,762
some kind of internal insight
on Yeouido Pirates.

549
00:38:27,263 --> 00:38:28,514
Yeah.

550
00:38:28,597 --> 00:38:31,183
They're spreading information
that disrupts the market,

551
00:38:31,684 --> 00:38:33,019
and you'll just let them be?

552
00:38:34,145 --> 00:38:35,146
Come on now.

553
00:38:35,688 --> 00:38:39,692
This "Captain" or whatever
needs to be captured for the public good.

554
00:38:40,359 --> 00:38:41,235
Come on, tell me.

555
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:42,903
You must know something.

556
00:38:45,614 --> 00:38:46,824
What are you doing?

557
00:38:46,907 --> 00:38:47,950
You punk.

558
00:38:48,534 --> 00:38:51,203
Can't you see I'm working my tail off
to make you president?

559
00:38:51,287 --> 00:38:52,121
Dad.

560
00:38:54,248 --> 00:38:55,875
The Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

561
00:38:57,335 --> 00:38:58,169
I know who it is.

562
00:38:58,252 --> 00:38:59,462
You do?

563
00:38:59,545 --> 00:39:01,672
Well, who is it? Tell me.

564
00:39:09,138 --> 00:39:11,015
- Oh A-ram.
- Oh A-ram?

565
00:39:11,098 --> 00:39:12,183
Oh A-ram, that punk…

566
00:39:15,353 --> 00:39:17,188
Wait, but you're Oh A-ram.

567
00:39:18,189 --> 00:39:19,106
That's your Korean name.

568
00:39:21,650 --> 00:39:22,485
Right.

569
00:39:24,487 --> 00:39:25,363
I am…

570
00:39:26,322 --> 00:39:27,156
the Captain.

571
00:39:33,913 --> 00:39:35,206
You damn punk.

572
00:39:37,458 --> 00:39:38,292
Why the hell…

573
00:39:39,502 --> 00:39:42,296
- Wait!
- Why the hell would you do that? Why?

574
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:43,506
Come on now.

575
00:39:43,589 --> 00:39:45,216
Just hold on! Stop.

576
00:39:46,175 --> 00:39:48,094
You're the one
who dragged me back to Korea!

577
00:39:48,177 --> 00:39:49,720
I did it because I was bored.

578
00:39:53,057 --> 00:39:54,517
Are you all right, sir?

579
00:39:56,143 --> 00:39:57,812
<i>I'm sure he'll be mad,</i>

580
00:39:57,895 --> 00:39:59,772
<i>but he'll have no choice</i>
<i>but to find a Plan B.</i>

581
00:39:59,855 --> 00:40:03,192
Because no one can know
that you're the Captain, Albert.

582
00:40:05,027 --> 00:40:07,571
Oh, we were just bored.

583
00:40:09,240 --> 00:40:10,825
It's a family matter. Get back to work.

584
00:40:11,742 --> 00:40:12,827
Yes, sir.

585
00:40:12,910 --> 00:40:14,328
Let's go.

586
00:40:19,875 --> 00:40:22,211
- You call yourself my son?
- Wait!

587
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:23,879
Wait a minute.

588
00:40:26,841 --> 00:40:31,303
Yeouido Pirates bought up
Hanmin stocks, right?

589
00:40:32,138 --> 00:40:33,305
Then they belong to us.

590
00:40:36,559 --> 00:40:39,019
Where did you get such an investment?

591
00:40:39,812 --> 00:40:41,063
You had the money?

592
00:40:41,605 --> 00:40:44,692
Shouldn't you be angry at me right now?

593
00:40:45,401 --> 00:40:46,235
No.

594
00:40:46,819 --> 00:40:47,820
Not at all.

595
00:40:49,780 --> 00:40:51,198
This is excellent news!

596
00:40:51,282 --> 00:40:52,199
We must remain calm.

597
00:40:52,783 --> 00:40:55,327
If the chairman finds out about this,

598
00:40:55,411 --> 00:40:58,998
he'll blow a fuse and accuse us
of scheming behind his back.

599
00:40:59,582 --> 00:41:01,167
Yes, Dad. That's precisely right.

600
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:02,501
Don't worry.

601
00:41:03,294 --> 00:41:04,628
No problem.

602
00:41:06,380 --> 00:41:08,257
Your dad will take care of this.

603
00:41:10,342 --> 00:41:12,052
Damn it. Why isn't this thing working?

604
00:41:20,728 --> 00:41:23,272
PERSONAL INFORMATION FORM

605
00:41:32,031 --> 00:41:33,449
According to my research,

606
00:41:33,532 --> 00:41:35,409
the real Captain is Korean-Japanese.

607
00:41:36,702 --> 00:41:39,079
He used a proxy to form a company in Korea

608
00:41:39,163 --> 00:41:40,956
to buy up the shares.

609
00:41:52,301 --> 00:41:53,511
Are you certain?

610
00:41:56,764 --> 00:41:57,973
Forgive me,

611
00:41:59,058 --> 00:42:00,392
but you share some of the blame, sir.

612
00:42:01,185 --> 00:42:02,019
What?

613
00:42:04,063 --> 00:42:05,981
With the president's seat remaining vacant

614
00:42:06,774 --> 00:42:10,236
and your heirs still too young,
opportunists are circling from all sides.

615
00:42:11,487 --> 00:42:12,321
Sir.

616
00:42:13,572 --> 00:42:15,699
Even if you can't trust me,
please trust Albert.

617
00:42:16,575 --> 00:42:19,662
He's still better than Nora, isn't he?

618
00:42:25,501 --> 00:42:28,462
I guess I should keep my word.

619
00:42:37,221 --> 00:42:38,973
PRESIDENT ALBERT OH

620
00:42:41,475 --> 00:42:43,602
"Oh Albert."

621
00:42:45,854 --> 00:42:46,689
It suits you.

622
00:42:48,274 --> 00:42:49,108
Are you happy?

623
00:42:49,191 --> 00:42:51,694
Oh, happy doesn't even
begin to explain it.

624
00:42:52,403 --> 00:42:55,447
Even one day in that president's seat

625
00:42:55,531 --> 00:42:56,782
makes a world of difference.

626
00:42:58,409 --> 00:43:02,830
I knew taking care of all this
before Nora came back

627
00:43:02,913 --> 00:43:04,915
was clearly the way to go.

628
00:43:05,874 --> 00:43:07,793
I saw on Yeouido Pirates

629
00:43:07,876 --> 00:43:10,713
that they call you
Oh Deok-gyu the Shadow Ruler.

630
00:43:12,756 --> 00:43:14,883
Those punks sure are witty.

631
00:43:14,967 --> 00:43:16,760
They're all just jealous.

632
00:43:17,344 --> 00:43:21,265
You know, your dad
had to plant countless alibis

633
00:43:21,348 --> 00:43:26,395
in every outlet imaginable
to trick the ever-distrustful chairman.

634
00:43:26,478 --> 00:43:28,188
You have no idea.

635
00:43:29,189 --> 00:43:30,524
Now, my son.

636
00:43:32,276 --> 00:43:33,360
Just trust me.

637
00:43:33,944 --> 00:43:34,778
Got it?

638
00:43:40,784 --> 00:43:41,827
My handsome son.

639
00:43:47,958 --> 00:43:50,044
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

640
00:44:06,393 --> 00:44:09,938
<i>Can't you see I'm working my tail off</i>
<i>to make you president?</i>

641
00:44:10,022 --> 00:44:10,856
<i>Dad.</i>

642
00:44:11,440 --> 00:44:12,650
<i>The Captain of Yeouido Pirates.</i>

643
00:44:13,776 --> 00:44:14,610
<i>I know who it is.</i>

644
00:44:15,444 --> 00:44:16,487
<i>You do?</i>

645
00:44:16,570 --> 00:44:18,364
<i>Well, who is it? Tell me.</i>

646
00:44:19,698 --> 00:44:21,492
<i>- Oh A-ram.</i>
<i>- Oh A-ram?</i>

647
00:44:21,575 --> 00:44:22,826
<i>Oh A-ram, that punk…</i>

648
00:44:23,577 --> 00:44:25,746
<i>Wait, but you're Oh A-ram.</i>

649
00:44:25,829 --> 00:44:27,206
<i>That's your Korean name.</i>

650
00:44:27,956 --> 00:44:29,083
<i>Right.</i>

651
00:44:29,750 --> 00:44:30,584
<i>I am…</i>

652
00:44:31,543 --> 00:44:32,378
<i>the Captain.</i>

653
00:44:40,552 --> 00:44:41,512
Hold on.

654
00:44:42,388 --> 00:44:44,139
What are you talking about?

655
00:44:44,640 --> 00:44:47,893
Albert is what now, exactly?

656
00:44:47,976 --> 00:44:49,269
Albert is…

657
00:44:50,604 --> 00:44:52,815
the one you ordered them to find, sir.

658
00:44:53,732 --> 00:44:54,900
The Captain…

659
00:44:55,943 --> 00:44:57,194
of Yeouido Pirates.

660
00:44:58,570 --> 00:44:59,530
Unbelievable.

661
00:45:00,280 --> 00:45:01,990
Look here.

662
00:45:02,074 --> 00:45:05,786
I thoroughly assessed everything
and completed due diligence

663
00:45:05,869 --> 00:45:09,748
before I decided to
appoint Albert as president!

664
00:45:09,832 --> 00:45:10,833
It seems

665
00:45:11,542 --> 00:45:14,253
that Executive Director Oh deceived you

666
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:16,463
to make Albert the president.

667
00:45:16,547 --> 00:45:18,549
Good grief.

668
00:45:19,174 --> 00:45:21,218
My goodness.

669
00:45:27,516 --> 00:45:28,350
<i>Oh A-ram.</i>

670
00:45:29,059 --> 00:45:29,935
<i>I am…</i>

671
00:45:31,228 --> 00:45:32,104
<i>the Captain.</i>

672
00:45:33,730 --> 00:45:36,483
<i>If the chairman finds out about this,</i>

673
00:45:36,567 --> 00:45:40,362
<i>he'll blow a fuse and accuse us</i>
<i>of scheming behind his back.</i>

674
00:45:41,447 --> 00:45:43,198
<i>Yes, Dad. That's precisely right.</i>

675
00:45:43,282 --> 00:45:44,408
<i>Don't worry.</i>

676
00:45:45,200 --> 00:45:46,660
<i>No problem.</i>

677
00:45:46,743 --> 00:45:49,037
<i>Your dad will take care of this.</i>

678
00:45:53,250 --> 00:45:54,626
That's not all.

679
00:45:56,420 --> 00:45:57,838
Recently,

680
00:45:58,964 --> 00:46:02,926
Executive Director Oh sold off
his nine percent stake in the company.

681
00:46:04,094 --> 00:46:05,262
And

682
00:46:05,345 --> 00:46:08,932
the slush fund
hidden under the OW was looted.

683
00:46:10,350 --> 00:46:11,894
I've confirmed Executive Director Oh

684
00:46:13,187 --> 00:46:14,021
was behind it.

685
00:46:15,856 --> 00:46:17,733
Oh Deok-gyu!

686
00:46:25,115 --> 00:46:27,284
What he did was incredibly immature.

687
00:46:29,036 --> 00:46:30,579
He regrets his actions deeply.

688
00:46:31,163 --> 00:46:32,539
I should've taught him better.

689
00:46:33,207 --> 00:46:34,583
Please forgive him, just this once.

690
00:46:34,666 --> 00:46:35,584
Do you think

691
00:46:36,543 --> 00:46:39,588
I'm this upset
about some internet foolery?

692
00:46:40,881 --> 00:46:42,132
You!

693
00:46:42,216 --> 00:46:44,259
Where did you sell off

694
00:46:44,843 --> 00:46:46,720
your nine percent stake in the company?

695
00:46:47,513 --> 00:46:48,514
That's…

696
00:46:49,306 --> 00:46:50,349
Not only that,

697
00:46:51,433 --> 00:46:54,144
you even touched the slush fund?

698
00:46:54,645 --> 00:46:55,729
A slush fund?

699
00:46:56,355 --> 00:46:58,065
I really don't know
anything about that, sir.

700
00:46:58,148 --> 00:46:59,525
- You don't?
- No.

701
00:47:00,192 --> 00:47:01,026
What's going on?

702
00:47:02,152 --> 00:47:05,197
Explain to me
what happened to your shares first!

703
00:47:09,284 --> 00:47:10,202
I screwed up.

704
00:47:11,245 --> 00:47:12,329
Be quiet.

705
00:47:12,412 --> 00:47:14,331
You stop it, Dad.

706
00:47:14,915 --> 00:47:16,625
You think Grandpa will go broke over that?

707
00:47:16,708 --> 00:47:17,793
You think we will?

708
00:47:24,174 --> 00:47:26,134
If you're curious
about the shares he sold,

709
00:47:27,386 --> 00:47:28,971
then answer my question first.

710
00:47:32,558 --> 00:47:33,892
Uncle Myeong-hwi's car accident…

711
00:47:35,686 --> 00:47:36,853
You instigated it, didn't you?

712
00:47:39,231 --> 00:47:40,315
What did you just say?

713
00:47:40,399 --> 00:47:42,818
He was trying to get you
to cooperate in the slush fund probe.

714
00:47:44,111 --> 00:47:47,072
You considered that a betrayal
and killed him off, didn't you?

715
00:47:47,155 --> 00:47:48,699
Why you little…

716
00:47:59,084 --> 00:48:01,128
What's the point of having family

717
00:48:02,129 --> 00:48:05,507
when they're all seeking their chance
to stab me in the back?

718
00:48:06,925 --> 00:48:08,260
Both of you!

719
00:48:08,844 --> 00:48:10,512
Get out of my sight.

720
00:48:10,596 --> 00:48:12,598
Right now, you bastards!

721
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:13,974
Sir.

722
00:48:16,059 --> 00:48:17,978
- I know nothing about the slush fund--
- Let go!

723
00:48:18,061 --> 00:48:18,979
Father!

724
00:48:19,479 --> 00:48:21,690
You know me.
This is a grave misunderstanding!

725
00:48:22,190 --> 00:48:24,526
I swear I know nothing
about the slush fund!

726
00:48:25,235 --> 00:48:26,361
Chairman!

727
00:48:27,446 --> 00:48:29,448
Oh god…

728
00:48:42,919 --> 00:48:43,754
We've…

729
00:48:45,380 --> 00:48:47,341
been played by that woman, Song Ju-ran.

730
00:48:48,592 --> 00:48:50,886
She waited for you to become president,

731
00:48:51,386 --> 00:48:52,721
and then set off that bomb…

732
00:48:54,514 --> 00:48:56,016
to get rid of us in one go.

733
00:48:58,185 --> 00:48:59,519
You knew about it, didn't you?

734
00:49:01,521 --> 00:49:02,939
That Uncle Myeong-hwi's accident

735
00:49:04,524 --> 00:49:05,734
wasn't really an accident.

736
00:49:08,528 --> 00:49:09,863
Isn't that why…

737
00:49:11,782 --> 00:49:13,492
you threw that punch in front of Grandpa?

738
00:49:17,537 --> 00:49:19,665
What does it matter
if it was an accident or not?

739
00:49:21,917 --> 00:49:24,211
We only got our chance
because Kang Myeong-hwi died.

740
00:49:30,300 --> 00:49:33,095
Even if I'd won Grandpa's favor
and things had worked out…

741
00:49:35,180 --> 00:49:37,140
I'd have ended up like Uncle Myeong-hwi.

742
00:49:38,392 --> 00:49:40,727
We should be thankful
we were kicked out and not killed.

743
00:49:44,022 --> 00:49:44,856
My son.

744
00:49:46,483 --> 00:49:49,111
We still have those
Yeouido Pirates shares.

745
00:49:49,695 --> 00:49:50,654
Right?

746
00:49:50,737 --> 00:49:51,655
Those are ours.

747
00:49:52,531 --> 00:49:55,117
If we use that as a stepping stone
and bide our time--

748
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:56,785
They don't belong to us!

749
00:49:58,120 --> 00:49:59,079
Please.

750
00:50:00,372 --> 00:50:01,456
Please just stop.

751
00:50:17,139 --> 00:50:18,181
They're not ours?

752
00:50:41,121 --> 00:50:42,164
Who is it?

753
00:50:44,708 --> 00:50:45,834
Your plan worked, Captain Hong.

754
00:50:46,543 --> 00:50:47,377
We got kicked out.

755
00:50:49,171 --> 00:50:50,005
Come in.

756
00:50:54,134 --> 00:50:58,013
Ms. Song framed my dad
for the missing OW slush fund too.

757
00:50:59,097 --> 00:51:00,390
That wasn't a part of the plan.

758
00:51:01,892 --> 00:51:06,146
That means Ms. Song
still hasn't told the chairman

759
00:51:06,229 --> 00:51:08,023
about Hong Keum-bo and Hong Jang-mi.

760
00:51:10,859 --> 00:51:11,693
Are you okay?

761
00:51:14,029 --> 00:51:14,863
I don't know.

762
00:51:15,489 --> 00:51:16,740
I'm officially penniless now,

763
00:51:16,823 --> 00:51:19,576
so you're responsible for me now,
whichever identity you take on.

764
00:51:21,161 --> 00:51:22,996
I don't have a cent to my name now.

765
00:51:23,079 --> 00:51:23,955
Call me Penniless Al.

766
00:51:24,039 --> 00:51:25,248
She'd better take care of me.

767
00:51:31,129 --> 00:51:32,297
ELIMINATING CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM'S
INNER CIRCLE

768
00:51:32,380 --> 00:51:34,424
STEP 2: ALBERT OH, OH DEOK-GYU

769
00:51:34,508 --> 00:51:39,054
ALBERT OH: ON OUR SIDE
OH DEOK-GYU: ELIMINATED

770
00:51:41,765 --> 00:51:42,974
Welcome back.

771
00:51:43,058 --> 00:51:43,892
Hello.

772
00:51:45,560 --> 00:51:46,937
Nora!

773
00:51:47,020 --> 00:51:48,772
Why didn't you answer my calls?

774
00:51:49,356 --> 00:51:51,691
Oh Deok-gyu and Albert
were kicked out of the house.

775
00:51:51,775 --> 00:51:53,068
The chairman made them leave.

776
00:51:53,693 --> 00:51:54,528
Why?

777
00:51:55,237 --> 00:51:58,240
They sold off company shares
and even touched the company funds.

778
00:51:59,074 --> 00:52:00,242
Oh my gosh.

779
00:52:00,325 --> 00:52:01,910
"Oh my gosh," indeed!

780
00:52:04,496 --> 00:52:05,831
Hey, where are you going?

781
00:52:07,040 --> 00:52:08,416
The office to say hi to Dad.

782
00:52:09,543 --> 00:52:11,837
Wait here so I can go with you.
Let me get changed.

783
00:52:19,094 --> 00:52:22,013
I just received word
that Ms. Kang has returned.

784
00:52:22,097 --> 00:52:24,683
I was worried she'd still be heartbroken
about the engagement,

785
00:52:24,766 --> 00:52:26,476
but I hear she returned in high spirits.

786
00:52:27,269 --> 00:52:30,230
She's on her way here to say hello to you.

787
00:52:31,106 --> 00:52:33,149
I could just see her at home.

788
00:52:35,694 --> 00:52:36,653
Ms. Song.

789
00:52:37,529 --> 00:52:38,738
Is there

790
00:52:39,781 --> 00:52:41,366
anything else…

791
00:52:43,326 --> 00:52:44,995
that you're keeping from me?

792
00:52:47,747 --> 00:52:49,583
Do you mean
regarding Executive Director Oh?

793
00:52:55,922 --> 00:52:56,798
No, sir.

794
00:53:15,442 --> 00:53:17,485
Let's see the results of your Swiss trip.

795
00:53:30,707 --> 00:53:32,709
You couldn't collect the slush fund,
could you?

796
00:53:33,209 --> 00:53:34,085
How did you know?

797
00:53:35,045 --> 00:53:38,173
By the way,
did something happen while I was gone?

798
00:53:38,256 --> 00:53:39,925
I heard Albert and his dad
were kicked out.

799
00:53:41,843 --> 00:53:44,179
President Shin ended up joining our side,

800
00:53:44,262 --> 00:53:46,765
and Albert has been
a part of the team for a while now.

801
00:53:50,560 --> 00:53:53,188
Queen Bee, can I ask you another question?

802
00:53:53,271 --> 00:53:54,272
What is it?

803
00:53:54,356 --> 00:53:56,691
What made you
decide to join forces with Ms. Hong?

804
00:54:02,906 --> 00:54:05,909
I've been beaten up
by all kinds of people since I was a kid.

805
00:54:07,702 --> 00:54:11,206
By my dad, my brother,
and older classmates at school.

806
00:54:12,707 --> 00:54:15,418
Sometimes it was with fists,
and other times, it was with words.

807
00:54:17,629 --> 00:54:21,091
People would look the other way
and walk past as I was being beaten.

808
00:54:22,342 --> 00:54:24,177
In my 29 years of life,

809
00:54:24,260 --> 00:54:25,720
no one stepped in to shield me.

810
00:54:27,973 --> 00:54:29,099
But Jang-mi…

811
00:54:30,600 --> 00:54:31,768
stepped in every time.

812
00:54:37,482 --> 00:54:39,442
<i>Well? Are you going to help her?</i>

813
00:54:39,526 --> 00:54:40,860
<i>Go on. I dare you.</i>

814
00:54:40,944 --> 00:54:42,487
How dare you try to hit a woman!

815
00:54:42,570 --> 00:54:43,446
Asshole!

816
00:54:46,366 --> 00:54:49,327
If you ever run that mouth
about Mi-sook again,

817
00:54:50,704 --> 00:54:52,163
I will end you.

818
00:54:52,247 --> 00:54:54,708
She did the same for Mi-sook, not just me.

819
00:54:55,250 --> 00:54:56,292
So I'm just

820
00:54:56,876 --> 00:54:58,628
paying back what I owe her
with my talents.

821
00:55:00,046 --> 00:55:01,631
I always pay my debts,

822
00:55:01,715 --> 00:55:03,800
and life is all about
"give and take," isn't it?

823
00:55:16,229 --> 00:55:19,232
You should appoint
Ms. Kang as the president.

824
00:55:21,151 --> 00:55:24,195
She wouldn't do anything foolish
like Executive Director Oh.

825
00:55:26,573 --> 00:55:28,783
If Nora becomes president,

826
00:55:29,409 --> 00:55:33,705
imagine how high and mighty
Choi In-ja will act.

827
00:55:34,414 --> 00:55:35,373
You know

828
00:55:36,291 --> 00:55:39,461
she wouldn't cause money problems
like Executive Director Oh did.

829
00:55:45,467 --> 00:55:47,010
There are times…

830
00:55:49,846 --> 00:55:51,931
I regret what happened to Myeong-hwi,

831
00:55:56,061 --> 00:55:58,480
even though it can't be undone.

832
00:56:01,733 --> 00:56:06,529
Check on the Swiss account
under Nora's name.

833
00:56:07,697 --> 00:56:11,785
We can't have another incident
like the one with Albert and his father.

834
00:56:13,578 --> 00:56:15,580
Yes, sir. Of course.

835
00:56:18,416 --> 00:56:19,417
All right.

836
00:56:30,804 --> 00:56:32,680
I went to Switzerland,

837
00:56:32,764 --> 00:56:34,099
and I even made it to the bank,

838
00:56:34,974 --> 00:56:37,393
but I couldn't withdraw the money.

839
00:57:07,423 --> 00:57:09,551
He asked if I knew
about the source of the funds.

840
00:57:10,218 --> 00:57:11,886
You told me last time

841
00:57:12,762 --> 00:57:15,348
that it was the secret slush fund
my dad kept.

842
00:57:17,267 --> 00:57:19,853
I got so scared.

843
00:57:22,230 --> 00:57:24,315
And President Shin also called me.

844
00:57:25,817 --> 00:57:27,444
He told me that if I was in Switzerland,

845
00:57:27,527 --> 00:57:29,612
I should come right back
without doing anything.

846
00:57:30,113 --> 00:57:32,866
He tried hard to stop me
over an international call.

847
00:57:34,159 --> 00:57:36,327
When did he make that call?

848
00:57:42,584 --> 00:57:44,586
I understand that you were scared.

849
00:57:46,087 --> 00:57:49,340
I was also scared when I withdrew
from Hong Jang-mi's account.

850
00:57:52,927 --> 00:57:54,637
You heard what happened to Big Al, right?

851
00:57:55,805 --> 00:57:57,891
You might be leaving Director Kang behind

852
00:57:58,475 --> 00:58:00,185
to become President Kang Nora.

853
00:58:05,732 --> 00:58:07,942
But I know it too.

854
00:58:08,485 --> 00:58:12,322
I know I could be kicked out
at any moment, like Albert.

855
00:58:22,081 --> 00:58:24,709
The Swiss account under Ms. Kang's name

856
00:58:24,792 --> 00:58:26,169
remains wholly intact.

857
00:58:26,669 --> 00:58:28,046
That's the balance statement.

858
00:58:35,303 --> 00:58:36,387
Let's proceed

859
00:58:37,472 --> 00:58:38,681
with Nora's promotion.

860
00:58:40,266 --> 00:58:42,227
When the storm hits,

861
00:58:43,144 --> 00:58:46,147
she could at least
serve as a shield for us.

862
00:58:54,531 --> 00:58:55,657
LUXURY WOMAN

863
00:58:56,366 --> 00:58:58,034
HANMIN'S HEIRESS, KANG NORA,
APPOINTED AS PRESIDENT!

864
00:58:58,117 --> 00:58:59,536
"A NEW ERA IN LEADERSHIP" AT HANMIN

865
00:59:00,912 --> 00:59:03,039
MS. CHOI DECLINES TO COMMENT
ON RECONCILIATION WITH CHAIRMAN KANG

866
00:59:03,122 --> 00:59:04,541
HANMIN'S HEIRESS, KANG NORA,
APPOINTED AS PRESIDENT!

867
00:59:12,674 --> 00:59:14,551
I mean, all I did

868
00:59:15,134 --> 00:59:17,470
was help put out a promotional article

869
00:59:17,554 --> 00:59:19,430
for the company and Nora's sake.

870
00:59:20,056 --> 00:59:22,392
Those reporters threatened me first.

871
00:59:22,976 --> 00:59:24,477
They said if we didn't go public,

872
00:59:24,561 --> 00:59:26,604
they would write
about the broken engagement.

873
00:59:27,188 --> 00:59:30,441
They also squeezed in
that reconciliation talk last minute.

874
00:59:33,069 --> 00:59:35,613
What exactly were you doing
while you let her do that?

875
00:59:35,697 --> 00:59:37,031
My apologies, sir.

876
00:59:37,740 --> 00:59:38,908
It was my oversight.

877
00:59:42,787 --> 00:59:45,290
Did the reconciliation rumors
rub you the wrong way?

878
00:59:46,416 --> 00:59:49,002
What's so terrible
about looking like amicable parents

879
00:59:49,085 --> 00:59:51,921
for the sake of Nora's career
and marriage prospects?

880
00:59:52,005 --> 00:59:54,299
Am I wrong? What is there to be mad about?

881
00:59:54,882 --> 00:59:56,551
Just think of it as a simple mistake--

882
00:59:56,634 --> 00:59:57,927
In my life,

883
00:59:58,428 --> 01:00:01,264
the biggest mistake
I ever made was you, Choi In-ja.

884
01:00:01,347 --> 01:00:02,181
What?

885
01:00:02,265 --> 01:00:05,184
Twenty-six years ago, and even recently,

886
01:00:05,268 --> 01:00:08,354
you used the kid as an excuse
to get yourself into this house.

887
01:00:08,438 --> 01:00:11,482
I should've turned you away
and shut you out then.

888
01:00:13,818 --> 01:00:16,029
Don't you remember
all that parading around…

889
01:00:18,364 --> 01:00:20,533
eventually got your kid abducted?

890
01:00:27,915 --> 01:00:29,083
Lie low.

891
01:00:30,043 --> 01:00:33,379
And refrain from visiting the office
for the time being.

892
01:00:43,389 --> 01:00:44,223
Damn it.

893
01:00:46,601 --> 01:00:47,685
HORANG AUTO REPAIR SHOP

894
01:00:52,315 --> 01:00:54,275
HANMIN'S HEIRESS, KANG NORA,
APPOINTED AS PRESIDENT!

895
01:00:56,194 --> 01:00:58,279
The kid's all grown up.

896
01:00:59,113 --> 01:00:59,947
She did.

897
01:01:01,324 --> 01:01:02,700
She even studied abroad?

898
01:01:18,007 --> 01:01:19,967
PRESIDENT KANG NORA

899
01:01:26,766 --> 01:01:28,059
<i>Congratulations, Ju-ran.</i>

900
01:01:29,477 --> 01:01:31,521
I saw that article on Kang Nora.

901
01:01:32,063 --> 01:01:34,482
I'm not the president,
so what is there to celebrate?

902
01:01:34,565 --> 01:01:35,566
Come on.

903
01:01:36,109 --> 01:01:38,736
All your in-house enemies are gone.

904
01:01:39,320 --> 01:01:41,364
It's your world now.

905
01:01:42,699 --> 01:01:44,784
I'm not as happy as I thought I'd be.

906
01:01:47,120 --> 01:01:51,040
The chairman also yelled at Madam Choi
over that article this morning.

907
01:01:52,500 --> 01:01:56,087
Maybe it's because
there's still a lingering threat?

908
01:01:59,841 --> 01:02:01,092
Hey, Ms. Song.

909
01:02:01,175 --> 01:02:02,260
You're already here.

910
01:02:03,761 --> 01:02:06,514
I see you still came,
despite what the chairman said.

911
01:02:06,597 --> 01:02:09,767
I couldn't just let my kid go alone
on a day like this.

912
01:02:10,268 --> 01:02:12,061
We just need to keep it a secret from him.

913
01:02:12,145 --> 01:02:14,605
Officially, Choi In-ja is lying low.

914
01:02:19,110 --> 01:02:21,154
Welcome, President Kang.

915
01:02:22,739 --> 01:02:23,614
"President Kang."

916
01:02:25,366 --> 01:02:26,868
Let's go and take that seat.

917
01:02:29,412 --> 01:02:30,246
Here we go.

918
01:02:30,830 --> 01:02:31,706
President Kang.

919
01:02:37,587 --> 01:02:39,172
My goodness.

920
01:02:41,424 --> 01:02:43,593
That seat was made for you.

921
01:02:47,138 --> 01:02:48,014
Ms. Song.

922
01:02:48,639 --> 01:02:50,850
You know you have to do
even better now, right?

923
01:02:55,480 --> 01:02:56,773
I'll give it my all

924
01:02:56,856 --> 01:02:58,941
to serve you
to the best of my abilities, ma'am.

925
01:03:02,069 --> 01:03:02,945
"Ma'am."

926
01:03:11,996 --> 01:03:12,997
It's so good.

927
01:03:15,166 --> 01:03:17,710
People would think you owned this house.

928
01:03:17,794 --> 01:03:20,463
They'd know he's a freeloader
with one look.

929
01:03:22,340 --> 01:03:23,633
I gave up my five percent,

930
01:03:23,716 --> 01:03:26,010
so you could at least provide
room and board.

931
01:03:26,511 --> 01:03:27,512
All right.

932
01:03:27,595 --> 01:03:29,263
As of today,

933
01:03:29,347 --> 01:03:32,558
Yeouido Pirates has amassed
19% of Hanmin's shares to become

934
01:03:32,642 --> 01:03:34,352
the second-largest shareholder.

935
01:03:36,187 --> 01:03:39,106
We'll shift our shareholding purpose
from passive investment

936
01:03:39,190 --> 01:03:41,275
to active involvement in management.

937
01:03:50,243 --> 01:03:52,745
YEOUIDO PIRATES DECLARES INTENT
TO PARTICIPATE IN HANMIN'S MANAGEMENT

938
01:03:52,829 --> 01:03:55,414
KANG PIL-BEOM, HONG KEUM-BO

939
01:03:56,123 --> 01:03:57,250
My head tells me…

940
01:03:57,834 --> 01:03:58,918
KANG PIL-BEOM

941
01:03:59,001 --> 01:04:00,169
…to join this side.

942
01:04:02,255 --> 01:04:03,256
But my heart…

943
01:04:04,882 --> 01:04:05,925
HONG KEUM-BO

944
01:04:06,008 --> 01:04:07,677
…tells me to join that side.

945
01:04:20,565 --> 01:04:22,608
So you're saying

946
01:04:22,692 --> 01:04:27,738
that Albert and Hong Keum-bo
are partners right now.

947
01:04:27,822 --> 01:04:28,656
Yes, sir.

948
01:04:29,615 --> 01:04:31,242
This is Hong Keum-bo's profile.

949
01:04:31,826 --> 01:04:34,662
- Goodness.
- She's a 35-year-old woman.

950
01:04:34,745 --> 01:04:36,205
Up until last December,

951
01:04:36,289 --> 01:04:39,667
she was a Capital Market Investigator
at the Financial Supervisory Service.

952
01:04:41,085 --> 01:04:42,712
The FSS?

953
01:04:44,130 --> 01:04:48,301
She was a part of the probe
into Hanmin's slush fund last July.

954
01:04:51,053 --> 01:04:51,888
Is that so?

955
01:04:51,971 --> 01:04:54,181
That must be why

956
01:04:54,807 --> 01:04:57,018
Albert asked about Myeong-hwi.

957
01:04:57,602 --> 01:04:58,853
We should start

958
01:04:58,936 --> 01:05:01,647
by looking into her intent
on attacking our company--

959
01:05:01,731 --> 01:05:03,566
No, not that.

960
01:05:03,649 --> 01:05:05,526
The intent is not important.

961
01:05:06,319 --> 01:05:10,823
What's important
is where she got that money.

962
01:05:15,953 --> 01:05:17,121
You dare interrupt a meeting?

963
01:05:17,204 --> 01:05:18,247
I'm sorry, ma'am.

964
01:05:19,707 --> 01:05:20,958
Mr. Shin Jung-woo

965
01:05:21,709 --> 01:05:23,753
is on the line,
hoping to speak to the chairman.

966
01:05:23,836 --> 01:05:25,046
Shin Jung-woo?

967
01:05:25,129 --> 01:05:27,506
He says he's representing Yeouido Pirates.

968
01:05:28,090 --> 01:05:29,508
What did you just say?

969
01:05:32,929 --> 01:05:33,930
Shin Jung-woo.

970
01:05:34,764 --> 01:05:39,518
I never thought I'd be
calling out your name again so soon.

971
01:05:39,602 --> 01:05:41,020
Things turned out that way.

972
01:05:41,103 --> 01:05:43,022
I'm calling on behalf
of our CEO, Ms. Hong.

973
01:05:44,607 --> 01:05:45,775
Why you little…

974
01:05:46,359 --> 01:05:48,736
You must be curious about
where we got the funds

975
01:05:48,819 --> 01:05:50,029
to purchase Hanmin stocks.

976
01:05:50,112 --> 01:05:51,489
<i>Yes, of course!</i>

977
01:05:51,572 --> 01:05:54,742
That's what I'm most curious about.

978
01:05:54,825 --> 01:05:57,203
I faxed a list of our funding sources
to the 12th floor.

979
01:05:57,745 --> 01:05:59,330
<i>Feel free to check for yourself.</i>

980
01:06:01,290 --> 01:06:03,000
Bring me the fax that just came in.

981
01:06:15,972 --> 01:06:18,766
HANMIN'S SLUSH FUND DETAILS

982
01:06:21,394 --> 01:06:22,436
Zero balance?

983
01:06:23,688 --> 01:06:24,689
Zero?

984
01:06:25,189 --> 01:06:26,065
What on earth…

985
01:06:27,233 --> 01:06:28,859
How the hell did this happen?

986
01:06:29,360 --> 01:06:32,196
What the hell happened here?

987
01:06:35,574 --> 01:06:36,826
CURRENT BALANCE: 0 WON

988
01:06:38,285 --> 01:06:39,954
JOGEOK BANK
CERTIFICATE OF ACCOUNT BALANCE

989
01:06:47,336 --> 01:06:51,048
That's the list of borrowed-name accounts
of branch managers and their families

990
01:06:51,132 --> 01:06:52,758
<i>that Hanmin used to hide slush funds.</i>

991
01:06:55,386 --> 01:06:57,680
<i>Our CEO wanted me</i>
<i>to thank you on her behalf.</i>

992
01:06:58,180 --> 01:06:59,598
Thank you for the funds.

993
01:07:07,815 --> 01:07:11,318
Goddamn it!

994
01:07:17,199 --> 01:07:18,159
Damn it.

995
01:07:21,829 --> 01:07:23,497
I spoke to Chairman Kang

996
01:07:23,581 --> 01:07:26,333
and told him that his slush funds
were the source of our funds.

997
01:07:26,917 --> 01:07:30,087
Now that he knows they're gone,
he won't sit idly by.

998
01:07:38,179 --> 01:07:39,972
HONG KEUM-BO

999
01:07:44,810 --> 01:07:45,728
CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM

1000
01:07:45,811 --> 01:07:46,854
Albert.

1001
01:07:48,856 --> 01:07:50,191
Shin Jung-woo.

1002
01:07:52,276 --> 01:07:53,903
Hong Keum-bo.

1003
01:07:56,947 --> 01:07:58,449
You were foolish enough

1004
01:07:59,950 --> 01:08:01,952
to steal what belongs to me.

1005
01:08:04,455 --> 01:08:06,874
Now you must pay the price.

1006
01:08:20,179 --> 01:08:22,014
ULLALA CHICKEN

1007
01:09:12,857 --> 01:09:14,692
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

1008
01:09:15,568 --> 01:09:17,194
Yeouido Pirates hereby declares its intent

1009
01:09:17,278 --> 01:09:21,365
to formally participate in the management
of Hanmin Investment & Securities.

1010
01:09:21,448 --> 01:09:22,741
<i>How is it at the office?</i>

1011
01:09:22,825 --> 01:09:25,369
<i>The company morale is at an all-time low.</i>

1012
01:09:25,870 --> 01:09:27,913
This should be enough
to go up against Chairman Kang.

1013
01:09:27,997 --> 01:09:30,541
Are you seriously suggesting that
as an option right now?

1014
01:09:31,125 --> 01:09:33,586
He gave the order
to withdraw the VIP's slush fund.

1015
01:09:33,669 --> 01:09:35,254
<i>Are we sure we can touch that?</i>

1016
01:09:35,337 --> 01:09:37,298
We have to do everything we can right now.

1017
01:09:37,381 --> 01:09:39,091
<i>Why would I betray the chairman?</i>

1018
01:09:39,175 --> 01:09:40,676
<i>We need you to take a stand.</i>

1019
01:09:40,759 --> 01:09:41,969
<i>What is the agenda item</i>

1020
01:09:42,052 --> 01:09:45,347
<i>the Pirates want to raise</i>
<i>at the shareholders' meeting?</i>

1021
01:09:45,431 --> 01:09:47,349
<i>The removal of Chairman Kang Pil-beom.</i>

1022
01:09:48,601 --> 01:09:53,606
Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim
